<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-525-058  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 525 058.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>UNIX World  Sept 1989 v6 n9 p58(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Real-time in the real world. (applications of real-time UNIX;includes related article on standards)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Van Halm, Rochelle.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Real-time UNIX is widely used in aerospace, robotics, medicaldiagnosis, and other applications for its data acquisition,image-processing, and process-control capabilities.andP;  The operatingsystem can run programs once only available on proprietaryhardware and software systems.andP;  It controls an environment byresponding to external events and returning results fast enough toaffect the environment.andP;  Factory-floor process control is thelargest market for real-time UNIX, with objective-oriented,modular systems automating quality control.andP;  Scientificresearchers use real-time UNIX in robotics applications, and NASAis upgrading the technology in its mission-control center toreal-time UNIX and other industry standards.andP;  Picker InternationalInc, a manufacturer of medical equipment, chose a real-time UNIXoperating system to produce lower-cost CAT scanners.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     UNIXReal-Time SystemsApplicationsProcess ControlVendor-Supplied SoftwareSpecial-Purpose Computers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>